High grade walnut stock, adjustable cheek and butt, recoiless system The operating principle of the Beretta UGB25 Xcel semiautomatic gun with break-open barrel is based on short recoil, which keeps the internal parts of the gun clean even after prolonged use. The short recoil (and low barrel axis position) almost completely compensates for muzzle jump during firing, with quicker and easier realignment of the barrel on the target for the next shot. The low barrel axis position transmits the recoil forces in line with the shooter’s shoulder, thus minimizing felt recoil. The ergonomically rounded back of the light alloy receiver fits smoothly into the stock, allowing quick and instinctive target acquisition. The polished sides contrast pleasingly with the other matte anti-glare surfaces. The streamlined receiver and the newly designed fore-end with its extended checkered configuration combine to give the UGB25 Xcel an extremely attractive look. The cartridge carrier receives the second cartridge on the right-hand side of the receiver, making it immediately ready for use. It is chambered automatically through the feeding port after the first round in the cartridge chamber has been fired

Designed and built as the next generation weapon-mountable IR laser/ illuminator, it is the battlefield replacement for the venerable AN/PEQ-2A which has faithfully served US Military Forces and Law Enforcement Agencies for years. One of the key improvements in the ATPIAL is the addition of a co-aligned visible laser diode which increases functionality, allowing for use without night vision devices. The visible laser is co-aligned with the IR laser pointer, meaning a zero with one, insures the same zero with the other. This is extremely advantageous because you can positively zero or check your zero during the day using a simple boresight technique. The ATPIAL’s increased functionality comes at almost half the weight and size of its predecessor. Due to the successful fielding of this unit to the US Military and Federal Law Enforcement Agencies, Insight has recently made this unit available to state, municipal, and local law enforcement agencies.
We have been truly impressed with the ATPIAL, Insight hit a home-run with this unit. And, we are very excited to offer the ATPIAL to our Law Enforcement customers. The exceptional functionality of this unit gives you everything you could want in a single compact package. Its design seats the unit low on the rail, and wraps around the Picatinny rail for a snag-resistant, low profile. This is accomplished by utilizing a recessed rail-grabber mount. Half of the mount is molded into the housing, which is a tiny frustration since it precludes the swapping out of the mount for a throw-lever system. The recessed controls are located on top of the housing for easy access in the field with gloves. The body housing is constructed of a high-density/ impact polymer and feels extremely robust. The material takes a lot of weight out of the unit, which is appreciated during long deployments. The ATPIAL also features a rear-facing battery compartment which allows the user to remove the battery (we all know not to store our high-end NV and laser equipment with batteries installed, right?) without removing the unit. A molded-in lanyard loop rounds out the back. Windage and Elevation are adjusted with tiny screws on the top and sides of the unit. Each adjustment produces a positive click. Overall, this is one of our favorite new laser units.

The gun has a very old, very hard recoil pad and I have a replacement on hand that is included with the gun (see photo). I have since had back surgery and my doctors are discouraging me from shooting higher recoil guns.  I have not shot this, but there is nothing that makes me think it won't shoot reliably and well,  Bore is clean and bright.   Since this is 65+ years old and I have a C&R FFL, I can sell this out of state or on premises to Indiana or Ohio residents.
